## 2. Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) - Dashboard

Currently, the frontend uses role checks (e.g., `isSuperAdmin`, `isStudent`) to hide/show UI elements.

| ID | Scenario | Role | Expected Result |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| RBAC-D-01 | View Global Constraints | **Super Admin** | "Global Constraints" button is visible and clickable. |
| RBAC-D-02 | View Global Constraints | **Student, Faculty** | "Global Constraints" button is **hidden**. |
| RBAC-D-03 | View Global Resources | **Super Admin** | "Global Resources" button is visible and navigates to `/resources`. |
| RBAC-D-04 | View Global Resources | **Student** | "Global Resources" button is **hidden**. |
| RBAC-D-05 | Create Project | **Super Admin, Dept Admin** | "New Project" button is visible. Can create a project. |
| RBAC-D-06 | Create Project | **Student** | "New Project" button is **hidden**. |
| RBAC-D-07 | Delete Project | **Super Admin, Dept Admin** | Trash/Delete icon is visible on project cards. Can delete project. |
| RBAC-D-08 | Delete Project | **Student** | Trash/Delete icon is **hidden**. |

