## 3. Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) - Project Scheduler

| ID | Scenario | Role | Expected Result |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| RBAC-S-01 | Upload Excel File | **Super Admin, Dept Admin** | Upload icon is visible. Can import data successfully. |
| RBAC-S-02 | Upload Excel File | **Student** | Upload icon is **hidden**. |
| RBAC-S-03 | Auto-Schedule Button | **Super Admin, Dept Admin** | "Auto" button is visible. Clicking it triggers the scheduler engine. |
| RBAC-S-04 | Auto-Schedule Button | **Student** | "Auto" button is **hidden**. |
| RBAC-S-05 | Drag and Drop from Sidebar | **Super Admin, Faculty** | Unassigned items can be dragged from the Sidebar onto the Grid. |
| RBAC-S-06 | Sidebar Visibility | **Student** | The entire unassigned Sidebar is **hidden**. |
| RBAC-S-07 | Grid Interactivity (Drag/Drop/Pin) | **Super Admin, Faculty** | Existing grid items can be pinned/locked or dragged to other time slots. Empty slots show an "Add Class" hover hint. |
| RBAC-S-08 | Grid Interactivity | **Student** | Grid is completely **read-only**. Items cannot be dragged. No lock icons. No hover hints to add classes. |
| RBAC-S-09 | Room Configuration | **Super Admin, Dept Admin** | Settings gear icon is visible to configure rooms. |
| RBAC-S-10 | Room Configuration | **Student** | Settings gear icon is **hidden**. |

*(Note: Department Admin and Faculty backend specific data-filtering rules will need database RLS policies configured in the future).*

