## 4. Core Timetable Features

| ID | Scenario | Steps to Reproduce | Expected Result |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| CORE-01 | Custom Session Creation | 1. (As Admin) Click Add Session via Sidebar (+).<br>2. Fill out Course, Faculty, select Room.<br>3. Save. | Session appears in the Unassigned Sidebar ready to be dragged onto the grid. |
| CORE-02 | Drag Constraint Validation (Conflict) | 1. Drag an unassigned session to a slot where the Faculty is already teaching.<br>2. Drop. | Toast error appears: "Faculty conflict". Session remains unassigned. |
| CORE-03 | Auto-Schedule Execution | 1. Ensure Unassigned items exist.<br>2. Click "Auto". | Loading spinner appears. All/most items are placed on the grid without conflicts. Success toast shown. |
| CORE-04 | Export to PDF | 1. Have a populated schedule.<br>2. Click PDF Export icon.<br>3. Wait. | A formatted PDF matching the current view (Faculty or Student) triggers a download prompt. |
| CORE-05 | Persistent Storage | 1. Make changes to the schedule.<br>2. Refresh the browser. | The changes persist (currently via `localStorage`, later via Supabase). |
| CORE-06 | View Switching | 1. Toggle between "Faculty View" and "Student View" using the header toggle.<br>2. Use the dropdowns to select specific batches/faculty. | The Timetable Grid accurately filters to show only the relevant entries for that selection. |

